{"lemma":"لَيْتَ","slug":"لَيْتَ","root":"ل.#.ت","root_slug":"ل-_-ت","root_link":"/words/roots/ل-_-ت","pos":null,"pos_camel":"verb_pseudo","paradigm":[{"role":"present_nanana","form":"لَيْتَ","in_corpus":true,"count":6,"asp":"i","per":"na","gen":"na","num":"na"},{"role":"present_na--","form":"يالَيْتَ","in_corpus":false,"count":null,"asp":"i","per":"na","gen":"-","num":"-"}],"frequency_in_corpus":6,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"لَيْتَ","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":14},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["particle"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38153"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92%D8%AA%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"particle","gloss":"if only, I wish, would (would God) that...; expresses an unattainable wish","examples":[{"text":"لَيْتَكَ كُنْتَ مَعِي أَمْس!","english":"If only you had been with me yesterday!"},{"text":"وَيَوْمَ يَعَضُّ ٱلظَّالِمُ عَلَى يَدَيْهِ يَقُولُ يَا لَيْتَنِي ٱتَّخَذْتُ مَعَ ٱلرَّسُولِ سَبِيلًا\n يَا وَيْلَتَى لَيْتَنِي لَمْ أَتَّخِذْ فُلَانًا خَلِيلًا","english":"And (beware of) the Day the wrongdoer will bite his nails (in regret) and say, “Oh! I wish I had followed the way along with the Messenger! Woe to me! I wish I had never taken that one as a friend."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/laj.ta/","/let/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38153","headword_ar":"لَيْتَ","root":"lyt","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a word denoting a wish [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that"},{"kind":"text","text":"—;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I wish that"},{"kind":"text","text":"—;] (S, K;) generally relating to a thing that is impossible; rarely to a thing that is possible: (IHsh, K:) governing the subject in the acc. case, and the predicate in the nom. case, (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaA^an~a","text_ar":"كَاَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or [rather]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a","text_ar":"اـِنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", MF) and its coordinates, because it resembles verbs in their force as words, [being composed of at least three letters, and the last being meftoohah,] and in their admitting most of the pronouns as affixes, and in their meanings. (S.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota zayodFA *aAhibN","text_ar":"لَيْتَ زَيْدًا ذَاهِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that Zeyd were going;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] (S;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layotaniY faEalotu ka*aA waka*aA","text_ar":"لَيْتَنِى فَعَلْتُ كَذَا وَكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that I had done so and so."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (TA.) You say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layotiY","text_ar":"لَيْتِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layotaniY","text_ar":"لَيْتَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEal~iY","text_ar":"لَعَلِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laEal~aniY","text_ar":"لَعَلَّنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~iY","text_ar":"اـِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~aniY","text_ar":"اـِنَّنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lytnY","text_ar":"ليتنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is more common than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lytY","text_ar":"ليتى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; whereas"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEl~nY","text_ar":"لعلّنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is less common than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lEl~Y","text_ar":"لعلّى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) You also say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA layota","text_ar":"يَا لَيْتَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, would that"},{"kind":"text","text":"—;.] As to the saying of the poet,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"yaA layota A^ay~aAma AlS~ibaA rawaAjiEaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lanaA rawaAjiEa","text_ar":"لَنَا رَوَاجِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O, would that the days of youth were returning"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to us"},{"kind":"text","text":")!]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rwAjE","text_ar":"رواجع"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the acc. case therein as a word descriptive of state: (S:) or it is governed in the acc. case by a verb understood, as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqobalato","text_ar":"اَقْبَلَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdato","text_ar":"عَادَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or some other verb suitable to the meaning: so says Sb: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt","text_ar":"ليت"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the above verse may be used in the manner of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [see below], (S,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt","text_ar":"ليت"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in the manner of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wajadotu","text_ar":"وَجَدْتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[I found], (Fr, S, K,) in government, not in meaning, (MF,) as related by the grammarians on the authority of certain of the Arabs, so that it is doubly transitive, and used in the manner of verbs: (S:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota zayodFA $aAxiSFA","text_ar":"لَيْتَ زَيْدًا شَاخِصًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that Zeyd were going away, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) this is done to give intensiveness:"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one says,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for this purpose,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layota zayodFA qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"لَيْتَ زَيْدًا قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that Zeyd were standing"},{"kind":"text","text":") putting both the subject and the predicate in the acc. case. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layotamaA","text_ar":"لَيْتَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see De Sacy's Gr. Ar. ii. 63. ―         -b3-  See also an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lyt","text_ar":"ليت"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a subst. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sawofa","text_ar":"سَوْفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["IHsh","K","S","TA","Fr","MF"]}]}}